result.execSummary:
The defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
AS TO COUNT 1
Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence. Huber privileges apply ONLY FOR WORK AT THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Court objects to electronic monitoring. 

AS TO COUNT 3
Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence. Huber privileges apply ONLY FOR WORK AT THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Court objects to electronic monitoring. Court will stay the sentence and place the defendant on probation for 18 MONTHS.

Court ordered 90 DAYS condition time to be served at the House of Corrections. 

Conditions: 
-AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment. 
-Absolute sobriety, random drug screens. 
-Maintain employment and or school. 
-Complete 50 hours of community service. 
-No weapons. 
-Complete parenting classes. 
-Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges, to be paid by 10/26/2015 or a civil judgment will be entered. 
-Defendant to provide DNA sample and pay applicable surcharge.

Defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek in court with attorney Alexis Liggins.  Defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Parties have reached a resolution. 

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 3
Defendant waived rights and pled guilty.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire, Addendum, and Elements received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered.

AS TO COUNT 2
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on motion of the state, court ordered count 2 Dismissed, But Read In.

Attorney Alexis Liggins in court, defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek not in court, in custody.  
Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Hearing proceeded.  Bail arguments made by defense and the state.  Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.  Defense requests date for possible resolution of this matter.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 25, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Electronic Monitoring.
Court ordered defendant to be monitored by Drug Testing. 
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  

Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Defendant Darius Rodell Dolenshek in custody.  

Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  

DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for July 15, 2015 at 08:30 am.
